  "text": "Mansfield and Stein [CITATION_1] observed that intraesophageal acid infusion could increase airway resistance in asthmatic patients and that antacid therapy would reverse these changes. Davis et al. [CITATION_2] showed that the presence of acid in the lower esophageal portion can trigger bronchoconstriction in asthmatic children with a positive Bernstein test.",
